==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Herpes simplex
<hw>Her"pes simp`lex</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>either of two forms of herpesvirus infection, distinguished as
being caused by herpes simplex virus type 1 (HSV-1), which causes mostly
sores and eruptions around the mouth (cold sores and fever blisters) and
at other points above the waist, and herpes simplex virus type 2
(HSV-2), causing genital herpes. HSV-1 is also known in some cases to
cause genital herpes infections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Herpestes</ent>⟦br⟧
